Package: mlscluster
Title: Multilevel selection clustering algorithm
Version: 0.2.2
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Vinicius", "Franceschi", email="vinibfranc@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0006-9337")),
    person("Erik", "Volz", email="erik.volz@gmail.com", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6268-8937")))
Description: mlscluster is an algorithm that computes three statistics (ratio of descendant clade sizes, ratio of persistence times, and logistic growth rates) 
    for sister clades in huge time-scaled phylogenies. Clade-defining homoplasies are matched with these statistics and results for different cluster thresholds are produced. 
    Therefore, this method highlights mutations (or transmission fitness polymorphisms [TFPs]) which likely present different selective pressures within and between hosts 
    (multilevel selection). This package contains functions to (i) compute the multilevel selectives pressures across thresholds, (ii) perform statistical analysis and graphical 
    visualisation for all thresholds to identify lineages and genomic regions enriched for TFPs, (iii) quantify the false discovery rate for each threshold, (iv) generate 
    multiple lineage and gene-specific plots of TFPs for the threshold selected by the user.
